videos.headline: Guy scores first 5 points of game
videos.description: Kyle Guy gives the Cavaliers a quick 5-0 lead with a midrange jumper, and then a catch-and-shoot triple on the next possession.

videos.headline: Salt uses glass for and-1 finish
videos.description: Ty Jerome drops one off to Jack Salt, who powers up and finishes through contact for the bucket and a foul.

article.description: De'Andre Hunter had 15 points, nine assists and eight rebounds to help fourth-ranked Virginia beat Middle Tennessee 74-52 in the last first-round game at the Battle 4 Atlantis on Wednesday night.

video.headline: Key makes extra effort for and-1 after falling down
video.caption: Braxton Key misses his initial attempt, but refuses to give up on the play, recovering the loose ball and muscling home an and-1 after being knocked to the floor.

article.headline: No. 4 Virginia tops Middle Tennessee in Bahamas

images.name: Key makes extra effort for and-1 after falling down
images.caption: Braxton Key misses his initial attempt, but refuses to give up on the play, recovering the loose ball and muscling home an and-1 after being knocked to the floor.

article.linkText: No. 4 Virginia tops Middle Tennessee in Bahamas
article.story: PARADISE ISLAND, Bahamas -- De'Andre Hunter was everywhere for fourth-ranked Virginia, finishing with 15 points, eight rebounds and a career-high nine assists. "I thought De'Andre's completeness showed offensively and defensively," Virginia coach Tony Bennett said. The 6-7 sophomore's size and athleticism caused problems for the Blue Raiders on the perimeter. "We really spaced the floor (against) the 1-3-1 press," Hunter said. "And I was just looking for my shot when the guys kicked it to me in the corner." Kyle Guy also scored 15 points for the Cavaliers (4-0), who led 9-0 and 30-9. But they needed Guy's 3-pointer to start a 9-0 run after the Blue Raiders had clawed to within 38-30 early in the second half. Antonio Green scored 11 points to lead Middle Tennessee (3-2), which shot 39 percent. The Cavaliers advanced to Thursday's semifinals to face Dayton, while the Blue Raiders will face Butler in the consolation bracket.
